TITLE: Describing Color-Coding for Data Types in ComfyUI (Markdown)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet explains the color-coding system used in ComfyUI to indicate different data types for node properties, inputs, and outputs. It includes a table of common data types and their corresponding colors.
SOURCE: https://github.com/comfy-org/docs/blob/main/essentials/core-concepts/links.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: markdown
CODE:
```
## Color-coding

The data type of node properties is indicated by color coding of input/output ports and link connection wires. We can always tell which inputs and outputs can be connected to one another by their color. Ports can only be connected to other ports of the same color.

Common data types:

| Data type                          | Color                                                                                                              |
|------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| diffusion model                    | lavender                                                                                                           |
| CLIP model                         | yellow                                                                                                             |
| VAE model                          | rose                                                                                                               |
| conditioning                       | orange                                                                                                             |
| latent image                       | pink                                                                                                               |
| pixel image                        | blue                                                                                                               |
| mask                               | green                                                                                                              |
| number (integer or float)          | light green                                                                                                        |
```

