TITLE: Implementing Advanced Image Selection Logic in Python
DESCRIPTION: Updates the choose_image function to handle different selection modes based on color characteristics.
SOURCE: https://github.com/comfy-org/docs/blob/main/custom-nodes/walkthrough.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: Python
CODE:
```
def choose_image(self, images, mode):
    batch_size = images.shape[0]
    brightness = list(torch.mean(image.flatten()).item() for image in images)
    if (mode=="brightest"):
        scores = brightness
    else:
        channel = 0 if mode=="reddest" else (1 if mode=="greenest" else 2)
        absolute = list(torch.mean(image[:,:,channel].flatten()).item() for image in images)
        scores = list( absolute[i]/(brightness[i]+1e-8) for i in range(batch_size) )
    best = scores.index(max(scores))
    result = images[best].unsqueeze(0)
    return (result,)
```

