TITLE: Github Actions Workflow for Comfy Node Publishing - YAML
DESCRIPTION: This YAML configuration automates the process of deploying a Comfy custom node to the registry through GitHub Actions. Triggered by changes to `pyproject.toml` on the main branch, it uses a workflow to execute the Comfy publish-node-action. Requires storing API key in GitHub Secrets as `REGISTRY_ACCESS_TOKEN`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/comfy-org/docs/blob/main/registry/publishing.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
name: Publish to Comfy registry
on:
  workflow_dispatch:
  push:
    branches:
      - main
    paths:
      - "pyproject.toml"

jobs:
  publish-node:
    name: Publish Custom Node to registry
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - name: Check out code
        uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - name: Publish Custom Node
        uses: Comfy-Org/publish-node-action@main
        with:
          personal_access_token: ${{ secrets.REGISTRY_ACCESS_TOKEN }} ## Add your own personal access token to your Github Repository secrets and reference it here.
```

