TITLE: Steps for Outpainting Workflow Execution
DESCRIPTION: This snippet outlines the necessary steps to execute the outpainting workflow in ComfyUI. Similar to the inpainting workflow, it ensures that appropriate models are loaded and the input image is being processed correctly.
SOURCE: https://github.com/comfy-org/docs/blob/main/tutorials/flux/flux-1-fill-dev.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: plaintext
CODE:
```
1. Ensure the `Load Diffusion Model` node has `flux1-fill-dev.safetensors` loaded.
2. Ensure the `DualCLIPLoader` node has the following models loaded:
   - clip_name1: `t5xxl_fp16.safetensors`
   - clip_name2: `clip_l.safetensors`
3. Ensure the `Load VAE` node has `ae.safetensors` loaded.
4. Upload the input image provided in the document to the `Load Image` node
5. Click the `Queue` button, or use the shortcut `Ctrl(cmd) + Enter` to run the workflow
```

